class_notes: Online with Face-to-face intensives dates: TBD
course_description: This course focuses on the delivery of primary health care from puberty through menopause. Content will focus on preventative, sexual, and reproductive health care conditions. Principles of pharmacology, pathophysiology, health promotion, and cultural considerations are integrated throughout the course.
prerequisites: NRSG 701D and NRSG 704D and NRSG 706D or equivalent transfer credit as prerequisites.
